While its clear you spent time on this, I just can't bring myself to upvote this. Sometimes, the art didn't really go well with the whole thing. Having the entire SCP be about a webcomic with having none of the traditional format, not even a little bit of it, is really setting people up to downvote it since you'd have to pull it off really well or grab their attention enough to keep them invested in it. Unfortunately, this didn't really pull it off with me.

And then there was a panel where it was nothing but exposition. A giant wall of text that explains your SCP's anomalous properties. This panel was bad, in my opinion, because usually in webcomics, its generally a terrible idea to explain things in your story by using a giant wall of text. The problem there is that, it becomes such a chore to read when in the comic, you're meant to be entertained.



