I'm totally ok with comics, btw, and if this were more polished I'd 100% upvote this in a heartbeat. As it is now, it doesn't succeed in what comics do as a whole- establish pacing through paneling. That is to say, the way the story is told, panel by panel, is monotonic. The dimensions don't really change, neither do the perspectives, or other visual cues to imply a change in pacing, perception, action, or similar. This makes the comic read fairly monotonic.

At the same time, this is a nice idea and I am all for this idea, especially in this format. I just wish the new format itself was handled with the proper idea of how comics are exposed. But overall I think this is an exciting direction you're taking here, and I fully support this endeavor.








Living the dream, or dreaming the life?






