I fully agree with this comment. I do enjoy the concept here, it's something I wish I had the talent and ambition to do when I wrote my own comic strip SCP, but I ultimately feel that this doesn't really work as an SCP or a webcomic. As others have said, the structure of the comic itself is very monotonous, the exposition dump is not done super well and overall the comic isn't much fun to look at with the dialogue panels taking up huge amounts of space, lack of backgrounds, and sometimes cluttered art. It's not a hopeless endeavor, I think that with a few more iterations this could easily be awesome. The theme of needing there to be supplementary content in order to survive as a fictional concept is a really cool idea, I hope to maybe read a future version of this that fully realizes its potential.








